This paper is primarily focused on generative models and their optimization, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments conducted in the paper are on image datasets (MNIST, CELEB-A), which suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) is another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the applicability of their approach to sequential data such as speech and music, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and signal processing (cs.SD). Finally, the paper proposes a new optimization procedure for generative models, which could also be relevant to control systems (cs.SY).
